Documents the current release status of a `ctx-context`/"cage" tool suite, listing outstanding tasks with descriptions and difficulty ratings — a plain-text task tracker, not code. Points to `docs/DECISIONS.md` for architectural rationale and notes the "Last updated" date should be bumped when tasks are added or resolved. Two open items tracked: an end-to-end smoke-test fixture for a sandboxed workspace exercising hook injection, native Edit, `ctx-verify`, and egress/write isolation (hard); and improving error surfacing from "the cage" component (easy). No code, APIs, or invariants to verify — edits here are just task-list bookkeeping.